UADataType.Description: Defines an equipment resource or a piece of equipment, a quantity, an optional description, and an optional collection of properties.

Field.Name: ID
Field.Description: An identification of an EquipmentClass or Equipment.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Additional information and description about the resource.

Field.Name: EquipmentUse
Field.Description: Information about the expected use of the equipment, see the ISA 95 Part 2 standard for defined values.

Field.Name: Quantity
Field.Description: The quantity of the resource

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: The Unit Of Measure of the quantity

Field.Name: Properties
Field.Description: Any associated properties, or empty if there are no properties defined.

UADataType.Description: Defines the information needed to schedule and execute a job.

Field.Name: JobOrder
Field.Description: The job order

Field.Name: State
Field.Description: The State of the job order. The array shall provide at least one entry representing the top level state and potentially additional entries representing substates. The first entry shall be the top level entry, having the BrowsePath set to Null. The order of the subtstates is not defined.

UADataType.Description: Defines the information needed to schedule and execute a job.

Field.Name: JobOrderID
Field.Description: An identification of the Job Order.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Addition information about the Job Order The array allows to provide descriptions in different languages.

Field.Name: WorkMasterID
Field.Description: Work Master associated with the job order. If multiple work masters are defined, then the execution system can select the work master based on the availability of resources.

Field.Name: StartTime
Field.Description: The proposed start time for the order, may be empty if not specified

Field.Name: EndTime
Field.Description: The proposed end time for the order, may be empty if not specified

Field.Name: Priority
Field.Description: The priority of the job order, may be empty of not specified. Higher numbers have higher priority. This type allows the Job Order clients to pick their own ranges, and the Job Order server only has to pick the highest number.

Field.Name: JobOrderParameters
Field.Description: Key value pair with values, not associated with a resource that is provided as part of the job order, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: PersonnelRequirements
Field.Description: A specification of any personnel requirements associated with the job order, may be empty if not specified

Field.Name: EquipmentRequirements
Field.Description: A specification of any equipment requirements associated with the job order, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: PhysicalAssetRequirements
Field.Description: A specification of any physical asset requirements associated with the job order, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: MaterialRequirements
Field.Description: A specification of any material requirements associated with the job order, may be empty if not specified.

UADataType.Description: Defines the information needed to schedule and execute a job.

Field.Name: JobResponseID
Field.Description: An identification of the Job Response

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Additional information about the Job Response

Field.Name: JobOrderID
Field.Description: An identification of the job order associated with the job response.

Field.Name: StartTime
Field.Description: The actual start time for the order.

Field.Name: EndTime
Field.Description: The actual end time for the order.

Field.Name: JobState
Field.Description: The current state of the job. The array shall provide at least one entry representing the top level state and potentially additional entries representing substates. The first entry shall be the top level entry, having the BrowsePath set to Null. The order of the subtstates is not defined.

Field.Name: JobResponseData
Field.Description: Key value pair with values, not associated with a resource that is provided as part of the job response, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: PersonnelActuals
Field.Description: A specification of any personnel requirements associated with the job response, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: EquipmentActuals
Field.Description: A specification of any equipment requirements associated with the job response, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: PhysicalAssetActuals
Field.Description: A specification of any physical asset requirements associated with the job response, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: MaterialActuals
Field.Description: A specification of any material requirements associated with the job response, may be empty if not specified.

UADataType.Description: Defines a material resource, a quantity, an optional description, and an optional collection of properties.

Field.Name: MaterialClassID
Field.Description: An identification of the resource, or null if the Material Class is not used to identify the material.

Field.Name: MaterialDefinitionID
Field.Description: An identification of the resource, or null if the Material Definition is not used to identify the material.

Field.Name: MaterialLotID
Field.Description: An identification of the resource, or null if the Material Lot is not used to identify the material.

Field.Name: MaterialSublotID
Field.Description: An identification of the resource, or null if the Material Sublot is not used to identify the material.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Additional information and description about the resource.

Field.Name: MaterialUse
Field.Description: Information about the expected use of the material, see the ISA 95 Part 2 standard for defined values.

Field.Name: Quantity
Field.Description: The quantity of the resource

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: The Unit Of Measure of the quantity

Field.Name: Properties
Field.Description: Any associated properties, or empty if there are no properties defined.

UADataType.Description: A subtype of OPC UA Structure that defines three linked data items: the ID, which is a unique identifier for a property, the value, which is the data that is identified, and an optional description of the parameter.

Field.Name: ID
Field.Description: A unique identifier for a parameter

Field.Name: Value
Field.Description: Value of the parameter.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: An optional description of the parameter. The array allows to provide descriptions in different languages when writing. When accessing, the server shall only provide one entry in the array.

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: The Unit Of Measure of the value

UADataType.Description: Defines a personnel resource or a person, a quantity, an optional description, and an optional collection of properties.

Field.Name: ID
Field.Description: An identification of a Personnel Class or Person.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Additional information and description about the resource.

Field.Name: PersonnelUse
Field.Description: Information about the expected use of the personnel, see the ISA 95 Part 2 standard for defined values.

Field.Name: Quantity
Field.Description: The quantity of the resource

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: The Unit Of Measure of the quantity

Field.Name: Properties
Field.Description: Any associated properties, or empty if there are no properties defined.

UADataType.Description: Defines a physical asset, a quantity, an optional description, and an optional collection of properties.

Field.Name: ID
Field.Description: An identification of a Physical Asset Class or Physical Asset.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Additional information and description about the resource.

Field.Name: PhysicalAssetUse
Field.Description: Information about the expected use of the physical asset, see the ISA 95 Part 2 standard for defined values.

Field.Name: Quantity
Field.Description: The quantity of the resource

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: The Unit Of Measure of the quantity

Field.Name: Properties
Field.Description: Any associated properties, or empty if there are no properties defined.

UADataType.Description: A subtype of OPC UA Structure that defines two linked data items: an ID, which is a unique identifier for a property within the scope of the associated resource, and the value, which is the data for the property.

Field.Name: ID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a property within the scope of the associated resource

Field.Name: Value
Field.Description: Value for the property

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: An optional description of the parameter.

Field.Name: EngineeringUnits
Field.Description: The Unit Of Measure of the value

UADataType.Description: Defines the information needed to schedule and execute a job.

Field.Name: BrowsePath
Field.Description: The browse path of substates. Shall be null when the top-level state is represented.

Field.Name: StateText
Field.Description: The state represented as human readable text. Shall represent the same text as the CurrentState Variable of a StateMachine would.

Field.Name: StateNumber
Field.Description: The state represented as number. Shall represent the same number as the Number subvariable of the CurrentState Variable of a StateMachine would.

UADataType.Description: Defines a Work Master ID and the defined parameters for the Work Master.

Field.Name: ID
Field.Description: An identification of the Work Master.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Additional information and description about the Work Master.

Field.Name: Parameters
Field.Description: Defined parameters for the Work Master.
